25 LC 112 3605
Senate Resolution 532
By: Senator James of the 28th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Serenity Empire Senior Living; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, founded in 2015 from humble beginnings, Serenity Empire Senior Living has
3 since grown into a thriving and respected network composed of seven senior care facilities
4 located throughout the State of Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, this distinguished organization has made history as the first Black-owned senior
6 living provider with multiple locations in Georgia, setting a new standard for quality and
7 compassionate care in the industry; and
8 WHEREAS, Serenity Empire Senior Living further holds the distinction of being the first
9 locally owned assisted living facility in the West Georgia area, delivering care that is deeply
10 rooted in community values; and
11 WHEREAS, at the core of its success is a team of passionate, loving, and dedicated
12 caregivers who ensure that each resident is treated with dignity and respect through
13 personalized care plans, wellness programs, and enriching community activities; and
